						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/New-funds-to-empower-women" title="New funds to empower women" alt="link">New funds to empower women</a></h2>

	
					<p> 
The New Partnership for Africa’s Development (Nepad) has signed a memorandum of understanding with Spain for the economic empowerment of African women. Nepad is now calling for proposals for unlocking women’s economic potential. Budgets should not exceed US$50 000 for national projects and US$250 000 for regional projects. A World Bank sponsored report on secondary education in Africa released in the first quarter of 2007 said educating women is a form of empowerment.Source: Research Africa, 10 August 2007 </p>
							<p><span class="date">24/08/2007</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/New-funds-to-empower-women">Read more...</a>
